Popular comedian AY has hailed the P-Square brothers, Peter Okoyo aka Mr P and Paul Okoye aka Rudeboy. The veteran comic act recently celebrated 15years of “AY Live” comedy show, an annual event where guests are thrilled with several performances from various artistes in the entertainment industry. This year’s concert which held on Easter Sunday saw the performance of Davido and P-Square. The P-Square duo enlivened the audience with their classics, some of which included “Forever,” “Personally” and several other hit songs.   Learn from mistakes not regrets – Burna Boy     Naira Marley asks fans if they will vote him as president     Wizkid laughs off Banky W’s interview   While appreciating as he anticipates another dose of pulsating performance from the Okoye twins, AY confessed their performance during the concert will remain unforgettable noting indeed they were born to entertain. He shared several photos of P-Square from the just concluded concert with the caption: Sometimes, we go apart to understand the true values of getting back together. “When two people are truly in sync, they always find a way of making things happen. This is one night I will never forget. @psquareworld were born to entertain. “One of my best wishes and decision for AY Live at 15, was to see these guys come together on the same stage…. PETER AND PAUL THEM BE ONE NO BE TWO.”